stylometry:
RISKSIMTABLE enables us to obtain a fair comparison quickly and easily. It shows the results of various inputs by running several simulations at once. We can enter a number of different inputs and see the results of each and be able to compar them to each other.
A good example is Walton's bookstore. We were trying to find the largest profit with different amounts of order quantities. We used 5 different order quantities and entered them into the simtable. We then ran it by having it run 5 different simulation with 1000 iterations each. It then showed us the results with charts, and we could also select standard deviation to be show as well.
